-- ECB says covered bond purchases total 28.529 bln euros
-- By Paul Carrel
-- Mon Dec 22, 2014 09:56AM EST
-- None



FRANKFURT, Dec 22 (Reuters) - The European Central Bank bought 3.773 billion euros ($4.62 billion) of covered bonds last week, taking the total amount it has spent on such debt under its new purchase programme to 28.529 billion euros.

The ECB said on Monday it had also bought 1.490 billion euros worth of asset-backed securities as of Dec. 19, an increase of 702 million from the prior week.  To read the announcement, click here: http://www.ecb.europa.eu/mopo/implement/omo/html/index.en.html